{
  "texts": [
    "They performed experiments on three modalities of medical imaging and organs using diversity of GAN designs, running from the simplest and foundational DCGAN to the most comprehensive style-based GANs.",
    "\"cardiac cine-MRI, liver CT and RGB retina images\".",
    "To gauge the visual acuity of the images produced by GANs, their FID score was estimated from training data taken from well-known and frequently used datasets.",
    "By evaluating the U-Net trained on these produced photos' segmentation accuracy, their experiment further evaluated the efficacy of the methodologies.",
    "The findings showed that not all GANs were created equal, with some being far better suited to applications in medical imaging than others."
  ]
}